FLEE: Attempt to escape from combat

Syntax: flee

DESCRIPTION:
  Attempts to flee from combat by moving in a random available direction.

  Success is based on your Physical Prowess (PP) stat:
    Chance = (PP / 30) * 100%
    Minimum: 30%
    Maximum: 95%

  Fleeing costs 1 APM (Attack Per Melee). If you have no APM remaining,
  you cannot flee this round.

  On success:
    - You move to a random adjacent room.
    - Your attackers lose their target (unless they give chase).

  On failure:
    - You stumble. No movement occurs.
    - 1 APM is still consumed.

NOTES:
  - The run command (if available) may function differently.
  - Aggressive enemies may follow you to the next room.
  - Stop attacking first with 'stop' if you only want to disengage
    without running.

SEE ALSO: stop, autoparry, autododge, kill
